    "minides": "Aston Martin's first-ever SUV — a Mercedes-AMG-sourced twin-turbo V8 wrapped in genuine British sports-car DNA, with the DBX707 holding the title of world's fastest production SUV.",
    "description": "The Aston Martin DBX is the British marque's first-ever SUV, launched in India in January 2021. It is powered by a Mercedes-AMG-sourced 4.0-litre twin-turbocharged V8, paired with a 9-speed automatic transmission and full-time all-wheel drive across both trims. The standard DBX V8 produces 542 PS and 700 Nm, while the range-topping DBX707 — named after its 707 PS (697 bhp) output — adds 900 Nm of torque, a new electronic limited-slip rear differential, carbon-ceramic brakes, and is currently the fastest production SUV in the world by top speed, eclipsing even the Lamborghini Urus. Both variants ride on adaptive triple-chamber air suspension with a 48V Anti-Roll Control system (eARC), and the cabin features Alcantara and leather upholstery, a 10.25-inch Mercedes-sourced touchscreen, a 12.3-inch digital cluster, 12-way powered front seats, and multiple drive modes including Terrain and Terrain+ for light off-road use."
  },
